To use gdb to debug IOS image:

The gdb program should be /router/bin/gdb-bleeding.ppc.

To start gdb session, do
  gdb-bleeding.ppc <ios-image>
      // The image name should be cat4000-i5s-mz.sun

  target cisco <term-server-ip>:<port number>
      // For my RFGW, it is "target cisco 172.22.71.19:2002"
      // This will attach the gdb session to the IOS session.
      // IOS should be up, or just load IOS image as normal
      // This should get you to the IOS prompt

  gdb kernel
      // To switch to gdb prompt.
      // Normal gdb commands, like setting break points

  cont
      // To go back to IOS

To quit, go back to the gdb prompt and type quit.


Commands:
  gdb-ios cat4000-i5su3-mz.sun
or
